history.content:
Hello, the class will not be expanded any further due to lab space constraints. We are at max capacity. You can use the 10% rule of thumb for drops.

EE16a is unfortunately a Phase 1 course.

children.subject: We are indeed constrained by lab capacity at this point.  If you've already taken Math 54 and are comfortable with linear algebra then 16B is likely a better bet for you anyways though - there are a bunch of threads on that topic here on piazza that I'd recommend taking a look at, but please also feel free to reach out to me directly if you'd like to discuss whether 16B or sticking with 16A is the best bet for you.

history.content: I just enrolled in ee16a and I'm on the waitlist at position 300. I'm a junior. Is the class going to expand? Am I likely to get in?
